Branches that are added to gcc:

gcc-kludges-meta
	Contains files which are relevant to the kludging of the history rather
	than the source tree you end up with.  Like this one.

	This is an orphan branch, effectively used as a separate repository.  I
	suspect some will say this is bad practice, and they might be right.

kludge-<release>
kludge-<release>-volatile
	The tree at each of these points is identical.  But if there is an
	update to kludge-<release> it will only be done by adding a new commit,
	i.e. it will always be a fast-forward.  kludge-<release>-volatile may
	be a rebuilt branch after an update.

